<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; <b>name:</b> talia al ghul
<p>&#9642; <b>age:</b> unknown (has the physical appearance of someone around 30)
<p>&#9642; <b>height:</b> 1.72m 
<p>&#9642; <b>hair colour:</b> brown
<p>&#9642; <b>eye colour:</b> green/brown eyes
<p>&#9642; <b>sexual orientation:</b> bisexual with a preference for men
<p>&#9642; <b>nationality:</b> middle eastern
<p>&#9642; <b>ethnicity:</b> arabic and chinese
<p>&#9642; <b>spoken languages:</b> english, french, italian, spanish, arabic, mandarin
<p>&#9642; <b>scars:</b> a small scar on her lower left abdomen, a medium scar on her right shoulder
<p>&#9642; <b>species:</b> human
<p>&#9642; <b>family:</b> ra’s al ghul (father), melisandre (mother - deceased), nyssa raatko (half-sister), damian wayne (son)
<p>&#9642; <b>occupation:</b> ceo of rastek industries, head of the league of assassins (splinter group separate from ra's al ghul) 
<p>&#9642; <b>base of operations:</b> gotham and nanda parbat 
<br /> <br />
<p>One of the world’s greatest spymasters, Talia al Ghul is a woman perpetually caught between the visions of the two most important men in her life: her father, Ra’s al Ghul, and her Beloved, Batman.
<p>“Talia,” as the Demon’s Daughter has simply been called for most of her history, has lived an extremely gendered life. Born into the highest echelon of the ancient and patriarchal League of Assassins, Talia could have had all the power in the world if not for the unfortunate happenstance of being born a woman.
<p>A peerless fighter and martial artist who possesses a keen mind for both strategy and tactics, Talia was nonetheless led to believe that the only way to secure the power lost to her by birth was to find a suitable male partner and produce a son. Yet, having accomplished both romance with her ideal man and the birth of a perfect heir, Talia was still left wanting. It was not until the Demon’s Daughter took her destiny into her own hands, forming the clandestine criminal empire known as Leviathan, that Talia al Ghul at last became something more powerful than even her venerable father could imagine.
<br />
<br />

<center><h3>early life</h3></center>
<p>In her youth, Talia travelled the world with her father learning and adapting his intellect and skills which she proves to be more competent than any of Ghul's other children. She excels to the point in managing his criminal and legitimate operations, that she is eventually appointed as Ghul's primary secondary despite the fact that Ghul considers women to be inherently inferior to men. Ghul is supportive of his daughter though has commented that if possible, he would correct "that sole failing" in his child suggesting that he fears any possible distortion of her through chemical or biological modifications despite his aversion to her as a woman.
<br /><br />

<center><h3>batman</h3></center>
<p>Talia first meets Batman when he rescues her from Dr. Darrk, apparently the leader of the League of Assassins. It is eventually revealed that the League is just one part of Ra's al Ghul's organization, The Demon, and that Darrk apparently turned against Ra's after failing in a mission (the usual punishment for this being death). At the end of the story, she shoots and kills Darrk to save Batman's life.
<p>When Robin (Dick Grayson) is kidnapped, Ra's al Ghul enters the Batcave, revealing to Batman that he knows Batman's secret identity and claims that Talia was also kidnapped along with Dick. Batman then goes with Ra's to search for Dick and Talia; it is revealed that the kidnapping was a setup designed by Ra's as a final test of whether or not Batman is suitable as an heir. Over the years however Talia has proven an important 'ally' in her way; most prominently, she encourages Batman to return to Gotham City when it is declared a "No Man's Land" following an earthquake, and he has lost his fighting spirit and didn't believe he could save Gotham.
<br /><br />

<center><h3>the red hood</h3></center>
<p>After Jason Todd's death at the hands of the Joker, Batman brought his body back to Gotham and buried him with the rest of the Wayne Family. However, several years later, during The Infinite Crisis, Superboy Prime trying to change reality, resurrects Jason with a reality-altering punch. Although Jason is returned to life, his body and mind are still broken from the Joker's attack. Some time later, he is discovered by the League of Assassins.Out of her love for Batman, Talia takes Jason to her father and Jason spends months in the care of the League of Assassins. Although his body recuperates, Jason's mind is shattered..
<p>Seeing no other way to help him, Talia takes Jason down to the Lazarus Pit and throws his body in while her father regenerates himself. Jason is fully revived in body and mind. Immediately afterward, in order to spare Jason her father's wrath, she aids the boy's escape.
<p>Livid at the fact that the Joker was still alive and that Batman had done nothing more than imprison him again, Jason pursues his own brand of justice. In order to stall him from killing Batman, Talia agrees to finance Jason and aid him in his training, so that he can become the second Red Hood.
<br /><br />

<center><h3>characteristics</h3></center>
<p>At first glance, she comes off as cold, calculating and discerning; much like her father. She makes no effort to show trivial warming to newcomers and she often despises most people she meets from the very first meeting. Her hard exterior is no doubt attributed to the strict and disciplined nature of her upbringing through Ra’s’ League and the various hardships she has endured throughout her life. She trusts very few people, and much of her actions are strengthened by the ideal that the only person she can rely on is herself.
<p>She is fiercely independent and protective of her feelings, but at the same time, has shown immense levels of heart. Her relationship with Bruce is incredibly unpredictable, but the bottom line has been shown on very many occasions that she still deeply cares for him.
<p>Talia is even more fiercely loyal to Damian, going to great lengths to ensure his protection; especially from Ra’s. Talia has turned on many of her allies in order to ensure Damian is safe and grows with a safe lifestyle. Despite early disagreement, she seems satisfied with leaving him in Bruce’s care.
<p>Despite all her motherly loyalty, Talia is still an incredibly deadly woman with years of hardened experience and no qualms about killing. She has shown time and time again that trust is a silent killer.
<p>talia can also be considered an athlete at the peak of physical conditioning and has been trained in many forms of martial arts. she also has a high intelligence, having advanced degrees in biology, engineering, and business as an mba. she’s quite proficient with most weapons and when it comes to hand to hand combant she is most often underestimated.
<br />
<p>&#9642; <b>longevity &amp; slow aging:</b> Talia is a regular human with no superpowers. Repeated exposure to Lazarus Pits has left her in peak physical form, perhaps as advanced as Bruce or the other elite heroes from Gotham. The pits have also increased her life span.
<p>&#9642; <b>businesswoman:</b> Talia possesses an excellent head for business.
<p>&#9642; <b>advanced martial artist &amp; hand-to-hand combat:</b> Due to her training, Talia is a master of both armed and unarmed combat. Her weapons knowledge extends from simple weapons to advanced modern weapons. She is also a master tactician, which has been necessary in her dealings in crime and espionage.
<p>&#9642; <b>high intellect:</b> Talia has a high intelligence. 
<p>&#9642; <b>master manipulator:</b> She is capable of controlling certain victims to her whim and is quite convincing and persuasive.
<br /><br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; The exact history of Talia has not been revealed thus far. In several alternate realities it is explained how Ra's al Ghul met her mother, who was of mixed Chinese and Arab descent, at the Woodstock Festival. Talia's mother later died of a drug overdose. That version was contrast to the early history which stated that Talia's mother was named Melisande and was murdered by a former servant of Ra's named Qayin.  
<p>&#9642; Ra's al Ghul successfully enlisted Batman's aid in defeating a rogue assassin who had murdered his wife. Batman was nearly killed protecting Talia from an attack by the assassin's agents. Talia gave birth successfully. The child was left at an orphanage; he was adopted and given the name Ibn al Xu'ffasch. The only clue to the child's heritage was a jewel-encrusted necklace that was given to Talia which Talia then left with the child. 
<br />

<center><h3>headcanons</h3></center>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>ptsd:</b> thanks to nyssa using her artificially created pit to kill talia and revive her over and over again, she suffers from post traumatic stress disorder (ptsd). her symptoms tend to come out after a stressful event, showing in the nightmares that plague her sleep. sometimes it will take something as simple as a car backfiring to trigger flashbacks of her sister shooting her over and over again before pushing her into the pit. she won’t admit that she has a problem as that would be seen as weak. anyone who is close to her will see that she suffers from something but unless she tells them about what nyssa did to her no one knows just what it is she suffers from.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>love:</b> love is not something talia feels. she was never shown love growing up and never knew just what it was supposed to be. while she does still love bruce it isn’t something that a normal person would consider love. the same can be said about the love she has for damian. having had no maternal figure in her life she tried her best to be a mother to her son. the love she has for him is closer to a natural love than that she holds for bruce. love also isn’t something she feels she’s capable of giving because of everything that has happened in her life. though a part of her would love the chance to find someone she could love and share her life with.</div>
<p><div id="hc"><b>languages:</b> talia tends to speak english most often. she knows french, spanish, italian, arabic and mandarin though mandarin isn’t one she’s fluent in as she learned it to honour her mother. all of the other languages she learned during her childhood because of the tutors her father hired to teach her. due to the amount of time she spent in london she has a heavy english accent and will sometimes use certain phrases common to those from england. arabic is something she uses during those times she visits ra’s. all the others are those she uses while she’s handling her business affairs.</div>
<p><div id="hc"><b>education &amp; business:</b>ra’s al ghul made certain that talia had all the best tutors he could find. during the first ten years of her life she was taught a myriad of things such foreign languages, math, science, and grammar lessons. he also made certain she was given a music teacher so that she had that knowledge when he found her a proper suitor. after the age of ten she was sent to london along with a small group of trusted league members to finish her education. ra’s expected her to return home once she was done with her education but finding out she was accepted into a prestigious university he allowed her to stay under one condition; she returned back to the fold once she was done.
<p>she did, of course, and was matched with bruce wayne. it wasn’t what she’d wanted in life and after producing the heir ra’s wanted she once again focused on her education and future. unfortunately, she waited until damian was safe in bruce’s hands before applying to and being accepted to cambridge’s business school. it was during this time that she came up with the concept of rastech industries. talia originally came up with it for a project during her time at school but once she graduated she decided to create the company. now, it’s on the verge of becoming an international company known for helping those in the third world get access clean water as well as offer microloans.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>fighting &amp; weaponry:</b>talia is an expert with a sword and with daggers in close combat. while she is also capable of hand to hand fighting, she prefers to use a weapon. her training came from her time growing up around the league. ra’s made certain she could handle herself and she took it one step further and decided to allow the members of the league to train her. like all of those who went through their training she completed it by killing one of her classmates and earned the mark that all members have on their bodies.
<p>when she’s out and about in gotham (or any other city) talia tends to carry two knives, one of which will kill someone with just one slice. during her time under ra’s tutelage she created a poison that has no known antidote. she is the only one who will survive getting cut by this particular blade as she worked to create it in the first place. anyone who ends up cut by it will die a slow, painful death; something she wanted when she originally created it. and every month she tends to re-coat the blade to make certain it hasn’t lost its effectiveness.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>ra's al ghul:</b> even though ra’s is her father, she doesn’t see him as such. he was rarely there for her growing up, using her as a pawn in his game. while he made certain she had the best tutors and the best trainers he was never the sort of person she would ever call father. ra’s never saw her as anything else but a pawn and talia knew she would never be good enough for him. she worked hard, she survived the training that all those who went into the league went through and even then she was still never good enough for him. he was cold, he was calculating and all he wanted from her was the ability to have an heir. ra’s also wanted someone who could take over the league from him.
<p>after forcing bruce to leave her, after leaving her son with the man she loved, talia made a point of taking her father down once and for all. her plan with nyssa had succeeded in an odd sort of way and yet ra’s still managed to survive. that showed her that she needed to be smarter than her father and instead of using her physical prowess against him, she went to business school and used those particular skills to beat her father. one day she does hope to take over the league. but until then she will use all her skills to improve the world.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>nyssa:</b> while nyssa is talia’s half-sister, their relationship is anything but. she never knew of nyssa growing up and once she found out she wasn’t certain what to feel for her. ra’s had never been a loving father and her mother had died young so finding out she had another sibling had come as quite the shock. as much as she wanted to accept nyssa for who she was, in her mind it was yet one more obstacle on her path to taking over the league from her father. though, they did find ways of working together she never fully trusted her sister.
<p>and like she assumed nyssa proved to her why she shouldn’t be trusted. ra’s was the only one she knew to have lazarus pits and growing up she knew they had to be in certain locations around the world. nyssa had somehow found a way of recreating them and had kidnapped talia knowing what would happen when one used them. over and over again she died, the pit bringing her back to life and leaving its mark on her. she knew why nyssa was doing it and knew that it was the only way they could bring down their father.
<p>it didn’t stop her from hating her sister and any time she sees nyssa she’s on edge. but there are times when they have an uneasy alliance to get done what needs to be done.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>jason todd:</b> jason todd was supposed to have been talia’s way of getting back into bruce’s good graces. she knew just how much he grieved at the loss of his robin and how he blamed himself. the lazarus pit was the only thing that could bring the dead back to life and it was her that stole his body from its grave. what was meant to have been something good turned into a nightmare and she thought it the worst mistake of her life. she had wanted to return jason to bruce as the robin he once was. instead, he was nothing than a shell of himself, reacting only to herself.
<p>it was then when she decided to take a different approach, treating him like her son in the hopes she could get through to him and send him back to gotham. she remembered that there were certain things bruce wouldn’t do and she decided that she would mould jason into the sort of hero that the city needed. talia set it all up and sent him away for the training she knew he would eventually need, always keeping tabs on him just in case something happened. each report had her smiling and she set it up so that he would be provided for while he set up his home in gotham.
<p>the one night stand was nothing more than that to her. she could never love jason. not like she loved bruce and she wasn’t going to tie him down. instead, she left him the one thing she knew he would use; his mask. talia knew that after that night they’d never be the same. she’d made a point of reminded him that she couldn’t love him and that his focus needed to be on gotham. in her heart she did care for him but it was never love.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>damian wayne:</b> damian wayne is the only other person besides bruce that she truly loves. she knows that she isn’t the motherly type, she knows she wasn’t a great mother to damian but she tried the best she could. while she was pregnant with him, talia had a hard time connecting with him in the womb. for a long while it actually felt surreal, like it wasn’t real. a part of that had to do with the fact that she’d lied to the man she loved and a part of it had to do with the fact that she never saw herself as a mother. but the moment she held damian in her arms she fell in love with her son. from that day forward she promised she would do whatever she had to do to keep him safe.
<p>as damian grew up talia made certain he had the best tutors she could find, similar to what ra’s had done with her. she also made certain that he was able to fight, that he could use knives, swords, and any other weapon that she’d been taught to use herself. being small in statue she also wanted him to be able to use that to his advantage. only when ra’s started to look at damian as his heir did she start to rethink him being under his tutelage. the last thing she wanted for her son was to take over the league. not when she had plans of her own. having her own son as the leader of the league meant one day she’d have to kill him to take what was rightfully hers.
<p>she knew there was only one person she trusted enough to take care of her son; bruce. as much as she hated to do it, she knew that her former husband was the only person that could protect damian. once again she packed up her belongings, she packed up damian’s belongings and dropped him off on bruce’s doorstep with a note asking him to take care of their son and to one day forgive her for keeping him from him. talia also reminded damian that he was more than a bat and that she loved him before leaving him behind. she always kept an eye on him, she made certain he was safe and while she hated that bruce had turned their son into a robin she wouldn’t ever interfere with that.</div>
<p><div id="hc">&#9642; <b>bruce wayne // batman:</b>bruce wayne is more than just her husband; he is the love of her life. other than damian, he is the only person she truly loves. talia fell in love with bruce after the other rescued her from doctor darrk. initially, she consented to being used as a pawn by ra’s to test whether or not bruce would be a suitable heir. she had heard of batman growing up and knew of his attempts to thwart ra’s attempts at using the lazarus pits, and it was why she initially consented. but after her rescue, seeing the way he handled himself in person and having to kill darrk to save him, she found herself falling in love with him. while their marriage was meant to be a way of keeping bruce as an ally and as an heir, and as a token of goodwill courtesy of ra’s, she saw him as someone who would actually love her. from that love came their son damian, and talia had every intention of making a life with bruce and their unborn son. but when the terrorists attacked them in the arctic, she was reminded that their life would never be normal, that they would constantly be a target, and she did what she thought was best; she used the stress of the attack to convince bruce she’d had a miscarriage.
<p>it pained her to tell him that and to watch him leave her behind. but in her mind it was what she felt was best. once things calmed down she put distance between herself and ra’s, and once damian was born she returned to the relative safety of ra’s and their compound. it wasn’t her first choice and if she’d thought bruce would open her with welcome arms after her lie, she would’ve gone to him. but she knew he wouldn’t forgive her for that. for ten years her heart yearned for bruce, and it was a combination of that and the fact she didn’t want their son to follow in ra’s footsteps that forced her to leave their son with the only other family he had. talia always had someone watching out for not only bruce but damian; not out of control but because in her heart she still loved him.
<p>one day she hopes to reconcile with bruce; if not for themselves than for their son. she has no misgivings in thinking that bruce still loves her like she loves him. talia is more than willing to accept an uneasy friendship between them. though given the fact that she still wants to fulfil her father’s goals and bruce will always want to stop her from doing that she knows that even a friendship would be difficult.</div>
<br /><br /><br />
</li>

