<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>early life</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Sophie Moore was born to Diane Moore and an unknown father and implied to have been raised in a conservative family. Upon discovering she was attracted to women, Sophie feared coming out to anyone, especially her mother, as Diane held prejudiced views towards LGBT individuals.
<p>In adulthood, Sophie studied at Point Rock Academy, where she developed a secret romantic relationship with her classmate, Kate Kane. The two often snuck off to make out despite the policy of "Don't Ask, Don't Tell", which was still in effect at the time. A week before graduation, they were caught by a superior and forced to reveal what had been happening. Given the option to deny the homosexual allegations, Sophie and Kate decided to tell the truth, feeling optimistic that the school wouldn't kick out their best cadets. Before that, Sophie asked the school not to call her mother, fearing Diane's reaction if she found out. Sophie was then visited by Kate's father, Jacob Kane who pointed out that Point Rock would just expel both her and Kate no matter what, despite the two being their best students. After this talk, Sophie decided to take the offer, wishing to graduate. As a result, she and Kate broke up.
<p>After graduation, Sophie went on to work for Crows Security, soon rising to become a high-ranking agent and earning the personal respect of Commander Jacob Kane. In 2015, she married fellow Crows agent Tyler. However, Sophie kept Tyler and her social circle in the dark about her orientation.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>rise of batwoman</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>In 2018, Sophie helped lead the team during an event in which the Bat-Signal was being turned off. During the event, Sophie sees someone in a white rabbit mask and proceeds to chase after them. She manages to grab onto the person wearing the white rabbit mask, but the two end up fighting one another. She then gets grabbed from behind after incapacitating the person in the white rabbit mask. She falls off the railing in the second fight, but her fall is cushioned. However, a Gang wearing animal masks takes her captive. She gets knocked out and is put inside a van. Later it's revealed that Sophie was kidnapped by Alice's gang, who wished to make a statement to Commander Kane.
<p>The following night, Sophie was taken as a hostage and made to stand on a plank of wood hanging from a skyscraper above the city's movie in the park event, Dodgson, one of Sophie's co-workers is seen walking to where Alice is keeping her, Sophie asks for help, but he's revealed to be working with Alice, as she tells her to have fun and walks away with Sophie calling him a traitor. The barrel holding the plank up was eventually slashed open, causing Sophie to plummet down, however, she was saved by a masked vigilante, who covered her as they crashed down into an abandoned building; and seeing the individual from up-close, Sophie could tell that her rescuer was a woman causing her to breath out that the latter was not “him”. Returning to work, Sophie caught a glimpse of Kate. She went to find her, thanking her for returning to help. They were joined by Tyler, whom Sophie introduced to Kate, who was emotionally hurt that her “old fling” settled down without her even realizing it up to that point.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>falling in love with batwoman</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>After divorcing Tyler and the Anti-Monitor crisis, Sophie begins a relationship with Batwoman, not knowing that underneath the mask is her ex, Kate Kane. Soon after, Sophie's boss, Jacob Kane, discovers that she helps Batwoman and suspends her. Later, she informs Batwoman of her situation, she says that she understands her, but at the moment where Batwoman leaves, Sophie says of waiting and they kiss.
<p>The next night, Batwoman goes to Sophie's home and they have an official first date. Batwoman wants to protect her and says that they don't see again because she has enemies and that they do the link she will be in danger, but Sophie answers her that she can defend herself, then they kiss. But Sophie's mother arrives, forcing Batwoman to leave.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>investigating lucius fox's murder</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Sophie met with Jacob who informed him that he was beginning to believe that someone in the Crows covered up footage from Sip&Dash on the night Lucius Fox was murdered. Sophie told him she had not changed her opinion on Batwoman, but she agreed to help him. Sophie went to the home of Alia Nazari, the owner of Sip &amp; Dash, to question her only to find her dead. Sophie was then saved by Julia Pennyworth from unseen snipers. Julia introduced herself to being another of Kate's ex-girlfriends, much to Sophie's surprise while taking her to Mary's clinic to treat a bullet wound that Julia received while protecting Sophie.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>returning to the crows</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Later, Sophie returns to the Crows on Jacob Kane's demand, and leads a new Crows strike team, together with Julia Pennyworth. She seems attracted to her. Later, after Julia has escaped from Hush, Sophie is reassured and kisses her. Julia kisses her too, and at this moment is when Kate arrives to speak to her.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>personality</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Sophie has a strong sense of justice. When Sophie discovered her sexuality, she feared coming out to others because she grew up with a parent who despised LGBT individuals. During her time at Point Rock Academy, Sophie loved Kate and eventually decided to reveal her sexuality to her fellow cadets, but after a chat with Jacob Kane, Sophie changed her mind and stayed at Point Rock though she regretted ending her relationship with Kate.
<p>Sophie struggled to be two different types; one where her family would be proud of and the other who was true to herself. However, after ending her marriage to Tyler and being in love with Batwoman, Sophie realized she could not be two separate individuals and decided to come out to her mother, even though this led to their estrangement.
<p>Sophie is proven to be very sympathetic as she comforted Mary who was grieving over her mother's death. Sophie is also proven to be a friendly individual as she quickly became friends with Julia Pennyworth, another ex-girlfriend of Kate's, without displaying any resentment towards her. On the contrary, she has started to develop romantic feelings for her.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>abilities</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>&#9642; As a graduate of Point Rock Academy and a member of Crows Security, Sophie is in top physical condition.
<p>&#9642; Since joining the Crows, Sophie has developed free-running skills and can fall from a height of several feet without hurting herself. Her abilities allow her to dodge and attack with fluidity from different directions without losing balance. She has shown to be capable of jumping off buildings with ease to apprehend a criminal from Alice's Wonderland gang.
<p>&#9642; Sophie is a highly skilled hand-to-hand combatant and martial artist, having years to hone her combat skills as an agent of Crows Security.    
<p>&#9642; Due to her Crows training, Sophie is highly skilled in the use of firearms.
<p>&#9642; Sophie is capable of fighting with knives, as seen when battling a member of the Wonderland gang.
<p>&#9642; As a determined and driven individual with training from the Crows, Sophie can handle the pain of a bullet wound. 
<p>&#9642; Sophie is very intelligent and an excellent investigator, as she follows every lead and rumor to discover the truth.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>equipment</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>&#9642; Sophie primarily makes use of a pistol, wielding it quite effectively. 
<p>&#9642; Sophie uses a combat knife in her battles.
</div>
<br />

<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; Sophie weighs 125 lbs
<p>&#9642; She has two degrees.
<p>&#9642; Sophie is possibly bisexual due to her marriage to Tyler and past relationship with Kate Kane. While her sexuality has yet to be confirmed, she will be written as bisexual with her interests being primarily with women
<br />


<center><h3>headcanons</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>&#9642; <b>sexuality:</b> for as long as sophie can remember she always struggled with her sexuality. growing up in a conservative family meant she struggled even more so than most. her background, particularly in relation to not only her family but specifically her upbringing as a whole, was steeped in compulsory heteronormativity from a very young age. this manifested in not only the belief that deviance from the norm of a nuclear family and the societally encouraged norms of marriage and domesticity were things to be avoided at all cost, but that any behaviours she might engage in that could be seen in this light was something that could lead to not only exile from her social & familial groups, but also the very real threat of bodily harm. except that sort of life didn’t make sense to her. in school she found herself looking at men and women, <b>and</b> then she would constantly hear her mother’s voice. eventually, sophie felt like she was broken, like there was something wrong with her because she wasn’t like the image her mother painted for her. it was something she constantly struggled with. even when she was accepted into point rock academy.
<p>their policy of don’t ask don’t tell made it easier for her to ignore the confusion that constantly bubbled to the surface. if anything could help sort her out she was certain the military could. until she met kate kane. at first they were roommates and would constant push each other to do better. but the more they studied together the closer they became. their first kiss clicked something in sophie that she never thought possible. and it showed her that she wasn’t broken. her interests just laid heavily with women instead of men. it also meant that the don’t ask don’t tell policy at point rock was going to make her life more difficult than anything else. she never complained and worked hard to be at the top of her class as she knew it was the only way she could have the sort of life she wanted.
<p>until they got caught. as much as she wanted to believe kate she knew she couldn’t throw the papers aside. she needed point rock and that meant locking everything up into a place where no one would ever find it again. sophie actually begged them not to call her mother because she knew exactly how that conversation would go. instead, she received comfort and guidance from kate’s father because he knew about his daughter’s sexuality. jacob helped her to see the unfortunate reality; that while kate might be free to exercise her privilege and go in, burning down the room around her, she didn’t have that choice. burning the room down around her, too, would end up ruining her life in ways she could never recover from. point rock also showed her that she needed to ignore her desires for women and focus on men instead. it’s why in the end she married tyler and why she told kate once again that they needed to keep their distance. sophie knows that kate is her one weakness and that if they spend time together it will reopen that part of her life that she’d buried after being caught at point rock.
<p><i>*the relationship with her family and the compulsory heteronormativity is one of the reasons why sophie developed perfectionist tendencies. in her mind it was the only way she could show she was just as good as the others in her class and the others she would be competing with as a crow. unfortunately, when she and tyler went their separate ways it was seen as rejecting that part of herself and led to estrangement with her mother. it also led to being told that her mother was disappointed in her because she rejected the life that had been created for her; something she’d been trying to avoid all of her life.</i>
</div>

<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>verses</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>main verse</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nleft"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/RiYICZ4.png"></div>
<b>the only thing i’m committed to right now is bettering myself</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → sophie ⸥ ❛ v; the only thing i’m committed to right now is bettering myself ❜ || main">threads</a>: this verse is mostly show based with a sprinkling in of certain comic elements. it follows sophie from her breakup with kate kane at point rock through her joining the crows and the struggles that  come with being the person she is. each series of the tv show will have its own arc.<br /><br /> 
</div>
<p>
<center><h3>canon alternate</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nright"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/RiYICZ4.png"></div>
<b>if someone says no you’re asking the wrong person</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → sophie ⸥ ❛ v; if someone says no you’re asking the wrong person ❜ || alternate">threads</a>:  sophie never ended up marrying tyler, instead sticking to dating him. when that eventually didn't work out, mostly because she couldn't give him what he wanted, she embraced who she was and started to date julia pennyworth, much to her mother's disappointment.<br /><br />
</div>
<center><h3>canon alternate</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nleft"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/RiYICZ4.png"></div>
<b>stories like the people who tell them aren’t always what they seem</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → sophie ⸥ ❛ v; stories like the people who tell them aren’t always what they seem ❜ || alternate">threads</a>: sophie and kate kane never got caught at point rock and were allowed to enjoy their relationship through graduation. unfortunately, not long after sophie's mother caught them which lead to them breaking up.<br /><br />
</div>
<p>
<center><h3>the old guard</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nright"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/RiYICZ4.png"></div>
<b>there isn’t one good thing in any of this</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → sophie ⸥ ❛ v; there isn’t one good thing in any of this ❜ || the old guard">threads</a> Her life had been planned out ever since she realised just what she wanted to do. Point Rock, the military and eventually the Crows. It was what she wanted and she’d risked everything to make that happen; even breaking her heart in the process. Sophie had known telling Kate to leave would hurt, but hearing about her death hurt even more so. The guilt kept piling on and while she was content in her relationship, it wouldn’t ever be enough. She worked her way up to second in command and her life was content. Until a ghost from the past. That was the catalyst for her eventual death, something she couldn’t prepare for. She’d been shot before, but this — this was different and had it not been for Kate she might’ve thought she was losing her mind. Waking up in her apartment had been strange. But not as strange as seeing the group of strangers surrounding her. In time she came to accept being immortal and while it meant leaving her life as a Crow behind at least she would have the familiarity of Kate by her side.<br /><br />
</div>


