<!-- jacob kane -->


<div id="07" class="popup_block">
<div id="popside">

<div id="popsideimage"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/1kieU28.png"></div> <!-- change the image on the popup sidebar -->

<ul id="poptabs">
     <li class="active" style="width:100px">biography</li>
		
     <li style="width:100px">headcanons</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">verses</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">connections</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">ships</li>
</ul>  

</div> 

<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<p>Jacob "Jake" Kane is a former USSOCOM colonel of the United States Army and the former head of Crows Security. He is also the brother of the late Martha Wayne, the estranged father of Kate Kane and Beth Kane, the widower of the late Gabi Kane and the late Catherine Hamilton-Kane, the estranged maternal uncle of Bruce Wayne and the step-father of Mary Hamilton.
<p>Jacob had Crows Security thoroughly investigated and those found being corrupt where fired or arrested. it took time but eventually jacob returned crows security to its former reputation and implemented a strict hiring process.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>personality</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Jacob was once a loving husband and father to his wife, Gabi, and his two daughters, Kate Kane and Beth Kane, however, after the car crash that killed his wife and supposedly one of his daughters, he became overprotective over Kate, his surviving daughter, deeming her as "everything he has left". Due to Jacob being overcome with grief over the loss, his relationship with Kate became strained, despite trying to give her a good future and accepting the woman she has grown to be, not particularly concerned that she is a non-straight individual. Jacob is proven to be deeply concerned about the welfare of others as when Alice had his second-in-command, Sophie Moore was held hostage, he pleaded her not to bomb all those civilians who were watching a movie at Robinson Park. The only reason Jacob formed Crows Security was to recruit ex-Navy SEALS and Green Berets to protect Gotham City and assist the GCPD in situations they cannot handle.
<p>Jacob firmly believes that justice can only come from law and order and disapproves vigilantes, such as Batman and Batwoman, describing them as a "symbol of false hope" and also blaming the former for the death of his wife and daughter due to failing to save them for the car crash. He also felt that vigilantes are liked by the city because they didn't subscribe to the rules, in his eyes, Batman is also responsible for creating the Joker and several other villains in Gotham's rogues gallery; completely disregarding the fact that Gotham was already a crime infested state to begin with, long before Bruce ever became Batman, as these said criminals would have emerged on their own, even if Bruce didn't become a vigilante in the first place. He was willing to go war with Batwomen instead of working together to capture escaped criminals and arrest anyone associated with her proving how far his hatred of vigilantes has costumed him. He also has no problem with breaking a truce as seen when he had the Crows kill Tim Teslow instead of letting Batwoman talk him down and attempt to kill her afterwards. This unknowingly strained her relationship with Kate, who Jacob never realized was actually the very vigilante he was trying to kill until she went missing and Alice told him the truth. This revelation caused Jacob to be overcome with guilt and remorse as he realized he tried to kill his own daughter and how it damaged his relationship with her.
<p>Jacob is proven to be extremely arrogant and self-righteous to the point that he doesn't take responsibility for his mistakes, blaming others for what happened to Beth only to later admitting it was a coping mechanism for not blaming himself and facing the truth that he was the one responsible for it; due to having stopped searching for her and believed that she was dead. Yet, he is not above apologizing or admitting when he was wrong. Also, even when having different view over something with one of his subordinate, like when he and Sophie disagreed about trusting Batwoman, he has demonstrated that he can be impartial on it, since what really matter to Jacob is to be able to trust his agents.
<p>Jacob knows that he can't talk his daughter, Kate out of anything once her mind is made up, as after she and Sophie were caught violating Point Rock Academy's strict code of conduct against homosexuality, he did not try to convince her to do what the academy's tribunal wanted nor explained to her that being one of it's top cadets doesn't get her special treatment or makes her above the rules, as he knew it would have been pointless.
<p>Jacob is proven to have loved Beth deeply; when he learned that his second wife, Catherine Hamilton, had paid the coroner to fake the DNA test over some skull fragments of a deer found by some of her men to make it match Beth's, he was angry, telling his second wife to get away from him and filing for divorce and in 2003 willingly trespassed August Cartwright's house after getting a call from Beth and tracing it there. While he was held captive by Beth he also broke down and confessed that believing Catherine was easier to him than going to bed with a broken heart, tearfully apologizing to his daughter for failing her. However, after Beth poisoned Catherine and framed him for her murder, he lost all hope that his daughter could be saved from the monster she had become and even ordered Sophie to have the Crows to kill her on sight. Also, he started to see Alice and Beth as two different individuals, declaring that whatever August did to his daughter erased any traces of her and Alice was mentally put in her place.
<p>Despite this, after learning that August has Alice tortured in an unknown location, Jacob immediately went to save her, threatening to skin August alive after doing so, after saving her, Jacob makes it clear to Alice that he still cares for her despite everything she has done, becoming even more sympathetic towards her after learning more of what she endured at the hands of Mabel Cartwright and what August did to her mother's remains but, despite this, he chose to lock her in Arkham anyway with Kate's help so she wouldn't hurt anyone else, though he was visibly solemn and saddened over having to do so, when he later visited her he explained that he had to lock her up so he can protect the only daughters he had left; Kate and Mary. In response, Alice vowed to make him suffer far worse than how she's suffering behind Arkham's walls, hearing this, Jacob was heartbroken on how far his daughter has slipped.
<p>Jacob is proven to have some morals; for example, after he discovered that Catherine had paid the coroner to fake the DNA test over some skull fragments of a deer found by some of her men to make it match Beth's, causing the entire city to stop searching for his second daughter, Jacob became enraged and disgusted to the point that he filed for divorce, yet that didn't mean he wanted her dead; when Beth killed Catherine and framing him for it, he was furious at what his daughter has done and filled with grief over his second wife's murder as well as the thought that his daughter could do something so horrible. However, despite this, he has not truly forgiven Catherine for her despicable actions and likely never will, and while he doesn't condone murder, he has obviously forgiven Alice for her actions after realizing the full extent of the abuse she suffered the hands of August Cartwright which was caused by Catherine, and he obviously stopped grieving; for her when he found out about the full extent of August's abuse. Despite being on the verge of divorce Catherine, that never intruded on his desire to still be Mary Hamilton's father-figure, since he love her and care very much for her well being. Additionally, despite having hated and wanted Batwoman dead, once he learned Kate was actually Batwoman, he immediately deeply regretted his treatment of Kate and continued to try to find her and hunt down whoever was responsible for his daughter's supposed death.
<p>Jacob has a homicidal side; as he tried to murder Kate (under the persona of Batwoman) in cold blood for no clear reason instead of just arresting her without; as he had no guilt, shame or remorse for this despicable act of his, he even planned to search for a bullet that could kill her as Jacob has no problem lying to his own step-daughter, Mary; since he lied to Mary when he made the alliance with Batwoman.
<p>But Jacob's attempt to murder the female bat vigilant in cold blood had unforeseen consequences; after a video of Jacob and his crows agents attempting to kill Batwoman in cold blood was leaked to the public; Crows Security gained a negative reputation, and the citizens of Gotham City have lost any trust and respect that they once had for the crows.
<p>Jacob had created the crows to protect Gotham City and he (delusively) believes that the crows are more effective than Batman; completely disregarding the fact that the Dark Knight protected all citizens of Gotham, regardless of whether or not they are upper-class, middle-class or low-class citizens without asking for anything; while the crows only protected upper-class citizens and get paid for it.
<p>Due to knowing the fact that Kate was Batwoman, Jacob is beginning to become more tolerant towards the new Batwoman, especially after the new Batwoman saved him from the False Face Society. Jacob went far as to acknowledge to Sophie and the Crows that he would be dead if not for Kate's successor.
<p>After Luke Fox was almost killed in cold blood by Russell Tavaroff, a corrupt agent of Crows Security, and after Jacob was almost killed by Russell and his posse, he realized the full extent of the organization's corruption; Jacob ultimately disbanded Crows Security; in order to prevent any more innocent civilians' lives from being destroyed by the crows. Jacob also realises that he is indirectly responsible for Crows Security becoming so corrupt; as for years he had been harbouring such despicable actions; but he overlook them; due the crows getting the job done, but they cross several moral lines in the process.
<p>While Jacob does care about members of his own family, he has a strained relationship with his nephew, Bruce Wayne, as seen when Tommy briefly impersonated him. It was implied that Bruce resented Jacob over wrongfully holding his alter-ego, Batman responsible for what happened to Gabi and Beth, as well as for having an unjustified hatred towards vigilantes in general. As a result; Bruce could never trust his uncle, Jacob with his secret identity as Batman.
</div>
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>abilities</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; <b>Peak of human physical condition:</b> As a former USSOCOM colonel, Jacob is in top physical condition for a man of his age. Jacob is shown to be quite fast for a man his age, as he was able to keep up with a former Navy SEAL or Green Beret like Chuck Dodgson. He was also able to jump on a car hood while running and has faster reflexes than a trained sniper. His conditioning lets him recover from most injuries very quickly, though not superhumanly, he went back to full health in less than a few hours after being stabbed in the stomach.
<p>&#9642; <b>honed senses:</b> Jacob has sharp hearing and sight, as well as keen skills of perception. He is able to pick up incoming danger and react quickly.
<p>&#9642; <b>Keen-level intellect/Expert tactician/Leader/Military training:</b> As the former head of Crows Security, Jacob is a highly skilled tactician and a capable leader. He also ran his security organization efficiently for over fifteen years and was capable of managing and organizing several handfuls of Crows Security agents by himself during countless operations.
<p>&#9642; <b>Skilled deceiver:</b> Jacob is proven to be a convincing liar, as he was able to fool both Kate Kane and Mary Hamilton to the point; that even Kate thought he was being honest; despite two the latters being excellent lies in their own rights. 
<p>&#9642; <b>Skilled investigator:</b> Jacob is proven to be a capable investigator.
<p>&#9642; <b>cellist:</b>  Jacob is a very talented cellist, having intensively studied the instrument growing up. He even taught his daughter, Beth Kane, how to play Bach's "Cello Suite No. 1, Prelude".
<p>&#9642; <b>basic medical knowledge:</b>  Jacob received medical training during his time in the army, allowing him to stitch up wounds. With this skill, he was able to lend a hand and successfully suture the wounds of a patient at his daughter Mary Hamilton's clinic.
<p>&#9642; <b>expert marksman:</b> As the head of Crows Security, Jacob is highly skilled in the use of firearms. He shot and killed the Executioner with a single round, as well as shot a sniper from a distance faster than him.
<p>&#9642; <b>Expert hand-to-hand combatant/Martial artist:</b> As a former United States Army and USSOCOM officer, as well as the former head of Crows Security, Jacob is highly skilled hand-to-hand combatant and martial artist, as he had received intensive training, as all U.S. Army members do. He managed to subdue Dodgson, a highly skilled hand-to-hand combatant in his own right, twice, despite the latter being at least a couple of decades younger than him. He was able to go head-on against Batwoman, although she was holding back at the time. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

