<b>a fine justification</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → ventress ⸥ ❛ v; a fine justification ❜ || the old guard">threads</a> alternate verse:   Hadriana was a name she knew once, before she’d been taken captive and thrown into the arena. Everyone knew about the gladiators. The Roman Empire had coliseums all over the empire to put on their games and to watch gladiators fight and kill one another. Not many knew about the gladiatrices. That had been her life; training and fighting in the hopes that one day she would gain her freedom. Unfortunately that day never came. It had been in the middle of one of the many games that the empire held when death finally came for her. She never thought she would come to life. Had it not been for Andromache she might’ve been buried alive with all the other bodies from those games. Instead, she travelled with the other, learning to fight and coming to terms with the fact she was now immortal. While she can fight she tends to stick to planning or helping those who joined them, helping them adjust to the fact they are now immortal.<br /><br />
</div>
