<!-- lanie blackstone -->


<div id="11" class="popup_block">
<div id="popside">

<div id="popsideimage"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/qB7Lvel.png"></div> <!-- change the image on the popup sidebar -->

<ul id="poptabs">
     <li class="active" style="width:100px">biography</li>
		
     <li style="width:100px">headcanons</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">verses</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">connections</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">ships</li>
</ul>  

</div> 

<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; <b>name:</b> Lanie Kara Blackstone
<p>&#9642; <b>age:</b> 31
<p>&#9642; <b>height:</b> 1.84m 
<p>&#9642; <b>hair colour:</b> dark brown almost black
<p>&#9642; <b>eye colour:</b> brown with hazel flecks
<p>&#9642; <b>sexual orientation:</b> heterosexual
<p>&#9642; <b>species:</b> pureblood witch
<p>&#9642; <b>nationality:</b> english
<p>&#9642; <b>occupation:</b> hit wizard with the department of magical law enforcement  
<p>&#9642; <b>additional information:</b> ferret patronus &amp; elder wood / dragon heartstring wand
<br />

<center><h3>the hit wizard</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Lanie’s story actually starts before she was born. It starts while her mother was married to a man she never knew; her biological father. Like most typical pureblood families, Kiara and Daegan were promised to each other after they graduated from Hogwarts. While not the “typical” married couple, for the first couple years of their marriage they were, for all intensive purposes, happy. Kiara went to begin her Healer training, and Daegan made an attempt at the family business. While the Blackstone’s had many businesses, Daegan was told to work in their magical antiquities shop that tended to carry items darker in nature.
<p>All seemed well until Daegan got bored, and decided to enjoy the bachelor life he never had, and could be seen on countless occasions on the arms of many different witches. As a faithful witch, and wife, Kiara silently stood by, deciding to spend as much time as possible at the hospital, instead of at home, knowing her husband had indulged in other women. This charade had gone on for a year, Daegan continuously photographed with high society witches, while Kiara worked. One night, Kiara came home early to find Daegan, in bed, with another witch, and obliviated them both.
<p>One month later, Kiara found herself pregnant, and left the wizarding world behind, deciding a life in the muggle world would be better than that she had been currently living. Kiara decided to keep her job as a healer, and it was during her lunch break at a nearby muggle café that she met Eli, her current husband. They fell in love and married seven months later, Eli not caring the child Kiara was carrying wouldn’t be his. When Lanie was born, she was given the Blackstone name, and formally adopted by Eli.
<p>Lanie lived what could be considered a “normal” life, knowing she could possibly be a witch. She did all the things normal muggle children did, and even made some friends. It wasn’t until after she received her letter to Hogwarts that she found out the man she had called dad all these years wasn’t really her father. It was quite the shock, and while she begged her mother for any and all information regarding her “other” father, Kiara all but refused. It had been eleven years, and Kiara wanted nothing more to do with the man she had called husband.
<p>Once she arrived at Hogwarts, Lanie tried her best to make friends, but found it hard with the information she had received from her mother still in the front of her thoughts. She put all her effort into her schoolwork, and any free time she had was spent in the library trying to find out exactly whom she could contact for information. Off the bat Lanie loved Charms, Transfiguration, and Potions, while absolutely disliking History of Magic.
</div>
<br/ >
<br />
<center><h3>life after hogwarts</h3></center>
<p>graduating as not only a prefect, but head girl, lanie had a myriad of choices when it came to her life post hogwarts. the department of mysteries came calling as well as the department of magical law enforcement. even though her mother was a healer, she never saw herself following that path. instead, she joined the ministry and started work in the law enforcement patrol. in time she worked her way up to the hit wizard division, where she currently works. there are times when she works with those in the auror division due to her skill set, but for the most part she prefers to keep to the hit wizard division.
<p>she currently owns a tri-level row house in notting hill, as well as a flat in sydney harbour. while her row house is situated in a muggle section of town, she's taken great care to have wards in place to keep them at bay. though, lanie has made exceptions for her neighbours and family just in case someone needs to get ahold of her. her sydney property only has one way in and out of; via portkey. and she's the only one who has it. it's also the only property with house elves, as she's taken precautions for them not to be seen by muggles.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>general appearance</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Lanie had always been tall for her age, and upon first glance, one would notice the young girl as being quite lanky, with most of her height coming from her long legs. At eleven years of age she already stood at five foot two inches tall, and according to her mother, would end up even taller by the time she was done growing. She may look like a pushover, but she is far from it, having grown up with a brother six years her senior. Her arms, while not well defined, have muscle tone to them, and the same goes for her legs, as her older brother was also into football. Looks can be deceiving, because if necessary, she can definitely stand up for herself in a fight.
<p>Her oval face is normally framed by her almost raven locks, which are sometimes kept tucked behind her ears. Her dark hair and eyes tend to stand out more against her complexion, which not olive in colour, but not pale, sickly white either. Her complexion could be considered medium, as she does enjoy spending time outside, and does tan up to a point. From far away, one would assume Lanie had a clear complexion, but upon closer inspection she has a speckling of very faint freckles across her face, arms, and shoulders.
<p>Lanie would definitely not call herself cute, but from afar one could get that impression with her pouty lips, and cute as a button nose. She’s definitely not your typical girl, and would call herself a tomboy instead.
</div>
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>dressing style</h3></center>
<p>Even though Lanie is a pureblood, she would prefer muggle clothing, like jeans and t-shirts to dress robes. When not in school, she can always be found in plain coloured t-shirts in a variety of colours, such as red, blue, green, or purple, paired with blue jeans, and combat boots.
<p>When it comes to jewellery, Lanie prefers to wear nothing but a simple watch on her left wrist. Anything else she considers too girly, and something she would never find herself wearing.
<p>She does not consider herself a slob, and tends to take pride in her appearance, making sure her clothes are wrinkle-free and her hair has had a brush run through it. The tomboy in her prefers things simplistic, and comfortable. If it is not comfortable she will not wear it.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>likes</h3></center>
<p>Lanie enjoys spending time alone, studying, or practicing the fine art of potion making. With her mother being a healer, her summers are spent learning to make potions, starting from the very simplistic with eventual goals of making the more complex ones. Lanie also enjoys learning charms or hexes, and looks forward to the day she can spend time in a proper dueling arena.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>dislikes</h3></center>
<p>Lanie dislikes those who play games and waste her time. She is an upfront and honest person, and prefers others to be more like her. She also dislikes those who don’t understand the concept of being on time. If she has to make the effort, than so does everyone else.
<p>When it comes to class work, she dislikes helping people unless she has something to gain from it. As for specific classes, she dislikes sitting through HoM, or Herbology, as they are boring, and she sees no use to them. She also dislikes flying as she is afraid of heights, though with the right person could be persuaded to fly.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>general personality</h3></center>
<p>Unlike most girls of her age, Lanie is not a bright ray of sunshine. She is a quiet girl, bordering on shy, but will voice her opinion at the opportune time. Her sarcasm tends to make her come off cold and uncaring; something for the most part that is true to her nature. For those that are patient, or stubborn enough to break through the façade she has created for herself, they will find that she is a caring person, and willing to do almost anything for them. Trust is something earned, not given, and with Lanie it takes a lot for her to give someone her trust.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>strengths</h3></center>
<p>Fortunately, or unfortunately, Lanie is loyal to a fault. She isn’t quite sure if that is a strength or a weakness at this point in time, but for now considers it a strength. When it comes to her friends she will defend them to the end. Lanie is also quite honest, to the point of being brutal about it. While many may find that a weakness, Lanie feels it is the only way to live, and expects the same from those whom she considers friends.
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>weaknesses</h3></center>
<p>One of Lanie’s major weaknesses is her quick temper. She has been known to lose it at the drop of a hat over the most miniscule things. She is also quite stubborn, and refuses to give up even if she knows she’s wrong. And along those lines, she refuses to believe she is ever wrong. If proven to be so, she will find a way to prove herself right again. Being quite headstrong, she tends to charge in first, ask questions later. Even though she grew up with an older brother, the concept of friends is something she has yet to grasp, only having a few acquaintances.
<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; lanie hates hosptials thanks to spending so much time in them as a child
<p>&#9642; she actually prefers muggle clothing to that of the wizarding world. When not working, she can always be found in plain coloured t-shirts in a variety of colours, such as red, blue, green, or purple, paired with blue jeans, and combat boots.
<p>&#9642; When it comes to jewellery, Lanie prefers to wear nothing but a simple watch on her left wrist. Anything else she considers too girly, and something she would never find herself wearing.
<br />

