<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>early years</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Lucie developed a love for writing when she was young. On her eighth birthday, James got her a thick blank book, which became one of her most prized possessions. She kept it next to her bed and copied her favorite pieces of her own work into it.
<p>During a trip to France with her mother, Lucie met and, in a span of two weeks, became very close to Cordelia Carstairs. They began to exchange letters every week In 1897, Lucie asked Cordelia to be parabatai and she agreed; though the ceremony was put off as the Clave wanted to make sure they were grown enough to decide. At the age of twelve, Lucie began to write a novel called The Beautiful Cordelia for her and sent her new chapters every month for four years.
<p>As of 1901, Lucie and her mother were teaching themselves Persian, with the occasional help from Thomas Lightwood, because Lucie felt she should be able to speak the same languages as her future parabatai.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>personality &amp; traits</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>Lucie rarely hides her feelings; she is straight-forward and would say whatever she is thinking without much second thoughts. Lucie can also be quite impetuous.
<p>Lucie is a writer, and she can't help but be intrigued by mysteries and romance. Lucie tends to make things up or guess circumstances creatively.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>physical description</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>Lucie has brown hair, inherited from her mother, and pale blue eyes that are a shade slightly lighter than her father's.
</div>
<br />

<center><h3>skills &amp; abilities</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p><b>Nephilim physiology:</b> Being Nephilim, Lucie is expected to possess a variety of enhanced physical and mental abilities granted to her by the angel blood of Raziel in her veins and also by the angelic Marks of the Gray Book. This includes enhanced strength, agility, stamina, and coordination, which would improve over time and practice.
<p><b>Runic magic:</b> Due to the angel blood in their veins, all Shadowhunters are all able to apply runes of the Gray Book on their skin without any real danger. These Marks, in turn, give varied effects that serve to benefit the wearer.
<p><b>Demonic magic:</b> Lucie is said to have special "talents" due to inheriting some demon blood from her mother. Her power allows her to see all kinds of ghosts and command them to do her bidding.
</div>

<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; She was named after Lucie Manette, a character in the book A Tale of Two Cities, a favorite of both her parents.
<p>&#9642; Like her father, she is the parabatai of a Carstairs.
<p>&#9642; Lucie, like her brother and cousins, can speak Welsh.
<p>&#9642; Her favorite book is The Castle of Otranto by Horace Walpole.
<p>&#9642; Lucie's favorite treat is bread and butter pudding.
<p>&#9642; Her weapon of choice is a throwing axe.
<p>&#9642; Lucie's favorite animal is a sparrow
<p>&#9642; Her brother, James, calls her Spots and Tuppence, among other nicknames.
<br />

<center><h3>headcanons</h3></center>
<p>coming soon!
<br />

