<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<p>eames is a man of many faces, and of many talents. professionally he’s a forger. probably one of the best you’ll ever come across. and not just real world forgery. he’s also the best at forging inside a dream. you’re probably thinking it’s nothing more than smoke and mirrors? only one way to find out…
<p><i>the following is considered public knowledge.</i>
<p>&#9642; <b>name:</b> eames
<p>&#9642; <b>age:</b> 42
<p>&#9642; <b>height:</b> 1.75m
<p>&#9642; <b>hair colour:</b> dark brown
<p>&#9642; <b>eye colour:</b> blue-grey
<p>&#9642; <b>sexual orientation:</b> indescriminate
<p>&#9642; <b>species:</b> human
<p>&#9642; <b>nationality:</b> english
<p>&#9642; <b>occupation:</b> thief, forger, artist, actor, flirt
<p>&#9642; <b>scars:</b> myriad of scars courtesy of bullets and knives. 
<p>&#9642; <b>identifying marks:</b> a smattering of tattoos across his arms, chest, and shoulders. (1. over his left bicep, there is a tribal design that has two poker chips hidden amongst the ink. 2. starting over his heart and going towards his left shoulder, there are the ace of every suit in a deck of cards, with the ace of hearts over his heart. 3. over his right shoulder blade is a tribal scorpion. 4. underneath his right arm is a chinese dragon 5. on his left hip there are the words ‘padre fiero’ 6. on his right bicep is an ode to his military past, also surrounded with a different tribal design)
<br />
<p><i>the following information is private, buried deeply and known to no one other than arthur.</i>
<p>&#9642; <b>name:</b> jamison harper eames
<p>&#9642; <b>birthday:</b> september 15, 1977
<p>&#9642; <b>family:</b> only child, no siblings, estranged from parents; wife, emily & daughter, cora killed in an accident
<p>&#9642; <b>occupation:</b> forger/thief for a criminal organization in london, as well as a dream forger/extractor
<p>&#9642; <b>other information:</b> ex-military, trained in demolitions; part time hacker
<br />

<center><h3>the man behind the fa&ccedil;ade</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>born september 15th to upper middle class parents, eames had as normal childhood as one could have given his circumstances. technically his parents were married, but to look at them one would have never guessed. living in an affluent part of london, he was given whatever it was he wanted, and then some. as a child it was the best thing that could have happened to him. unfortunately, as he grew up he found himself bored with having any and every thing just handed to him. he had always had a knack for art, and out of boredom turned to reproducing in sketch form the famous pieces of art that hung in his parents house. it was these reproductions that garnered the attention of his friends; friends who just happened to have criminal connections.
<p>During his last years in school, he would have preferred to have spent his time working on forgeries instead of his own school work. At night when he was supposed to have been studying, Eames could be found in a room with about a half dozen others working to perfect his craft. He absolutely hated it, hated the fact he had to make multiple copies of the same document until the man who’d brought him on was pleased with it. Some nights it could be two dozen copies, other nights it could be one dozen. Either way, he found himself reconsidering exactly what he was doing. It was only when one of the others he’d become friends with had gone missing did he realize that there was no way out. At least not completely.
<p>This went on for months &#8212; days spent pretending he was a student, while the nights were spent forging different documents. Most of what they had him work on were simple banking documents, wills, and the likes. Nothing that would be scrutinized too closely. And for the most part he was okay with that. Eames knew that it was better than sitting at home listening to his parents bitch about this and that and which functions they would all need to attend. Anything was better than that, and he actually worked hard at what he did, slowly working his way up the ranks so that one day he wouldn’t have to be the one doing all the grunt work.
<p>It wasn’t until one night, close to graduation, that he was caught. His parents were supposed to be out at some function, and instead they had decided at the last minute not to go. Eames was already at ‘work’ at the time, and had no idea until he returned to find them ready for some sort of explanation. It was one of the few times they were a united front. Normally, he could look anyone straight in the face and lie to them. His parents were the only exception. They knew he was up to no good, and left him with an ultimatum. Once he was finished with school he would be shipped off to the military, and he would cut ties with everyone that had dragged him into the life of crime.
<p>To say he was thrilled was a complete understatement. He just made more of an effort to conceal his work, though he also made it known to his employers that he would need to make his leave. Not completely, of course. Eames knew that wasn’t possible. Just long enough for him to complete his stint, and then he would return to work for them. His employers weren’t pleased but he had proved himself over the months, and they were willing to allow him to go with the understanding that once he was done he would return to work for them whenever they needed it. The deal wasn’t one he would have normally made, but knowing it was either that or his life he decided to take it. One day he would find a way to break away and make a name for himself. But until then he could handle the jobs they had.
<p>The military was quite the eye opening experience. He found out just how much he loathed killing people, or at least the possibility. If push came to shove he would do as ordered, but he never found the joy of it like some of the others in his company. The only thing he found he could marginally enjoy was the explosives training. Eames felt like he could be detached from the possibility of actually killing people. Oddly enough it was something he eventually thrived in, working his way up the ranks, and eventually becoming an expert. It was this expertise that lead him to being picked for a special forces unit, and eventually being chosen for Project Somnacin.
<p>And after that? Eames dropped off the map, and his history is a bit murky. Mostly dead ends, and false leads. No one knows exactly who Eames is, and it’s exactly how he wants it.
</div>
<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>family</h4>
<p>these relationships exist in each and every verse <b>no matter what</b>.<br /><br />

<center><h3>emily eames</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/7FM6UGB.png"></div>
<b>emily eames</b> &mdash; Emily was supposed to be nothing more than a one night stand, a drunken tumble between the sheets while on leave from the army. Eames had no plans on ever seeing her again. Not until she found a way of contacting him during his first month in his new military assignment. Upon finding out that she was pregnant, he told her that he would do the right thing, that he wouldn't just abandon her. And after sneaking off base, they were married in a small civil ceremony.<br /><br />
While Eames wasn't looking for love, he found himself falling more and more in love with Emily as they awaited the birth of their child. He even went so far as to introduce her to Benji and eventually the three of them were the best of friends. Emily was his world and he could never see himself in a position where she wasn't in it. Once their daughter was born the feelings only grew stronger. He loved his family, and enjoyed having them to come home to. Unfortunately, those he worked for found his new found loyalty a hindrance. It was a rainy night when Emily, along with Cora, were killed in a car crash. While local law enforcement said it was nothing more than an accident due to the weather, Eames knew it was more than that. He had no proof and as a criminal knew there was nothing he could do. With his world shattered, all he could do was remember the love Emily had given him.
</div>
<br />
<p>
<center><h3>cora eames</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/L41lf2z.png"></div>
<b>cora eames</b> &mdash; Cora was the light of Eames' life. More so than his wife. With curly red hair, and storm blue-grey eyes, she was a spitting image of her parents. She also took after her father with her stubbornness and ability to charm just about anyone she met. Which was a good thing most of the time. In those rare times when Eames needed to discipline her, he and Emily found out just how bad it was that their daughter inherited that particular trait. Of course she did inherit her mother's ability to sleep through just about anything, and her fashion sense. Eames did anything and everything for Cora. She thought him what it was to love unconditionally. It was a rainy night when Cora, along with her mum Emily, were killed in a car crash. With the light of his life gone, Eames found himself closing off to anyone and everyone around him, and throwing himself head first into work.
</div>
<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

