<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>&#9642; <b>FULL NAME:</b> Rowyn Finley Langston
<p>&#9642; <b>ALIASES/NICKNAMES:</b> Fin, Finley, Senior Officer Langston 
<p>&#9642; <b>DATE OF BIRTH:</b> June 6, 1981
<p>&#9642; <b>PROFESSION:</b> CIA Analyst (Chief Interrogator in Special Projects involving dreamsharing)
<p>&#9642; <b>SEXUALITY:</b>  Finley considers herself bisexual and asexual. When she does show interest in someone it tends to be more towards men than women. She’s extremely focused on the job and anything outside of that isn’t something she focuses on. If she does find someone attractive or if someone piqued her interest she will use what she’s learned on the job and call it flirting. She also prefers something casual instead of something long term. As a workaholic she has no time for relationships.
<p>&#9642; <b>BODY TYPE:</b> 5'6 in height, and roughly 150 lbs. She’s not stick skinny perse, but neither is she built. Finley has the muscle required of the job and from working out when she’s not at Langley.
<p>&#9642; <b>CLOTHING:</b> Finely definitely believes in professional attire. Anytime she’s at Langley you’ll find her in pants suits and heels, usually black or a mix of black and red or blue. She’s never been one to wear skirts and she avoids them as much as possible. When she’s not at Langley or when she’s off work, she will tend to wear jeans, a collared shirt and a black leather jacket along with combat boots. Comfort to most isn’t comfort to her and while she will wear sweats while at her brownstone in DuPont Circle. 
<p>&#9642; <b>DISTINCTIVE FEATURES:</b> Upon first glance, one tends to notice Finley’s hair. Depending on the light it will either be bright copper red or a faded red. The next thing people notice are her eyes. They tend to be a green blue and depending on the light they look either ice blue or green. When she’s angry they tend to take on a more green hue and when she’s calm they tend to look more icy blue. She also has a scar down the inside of her left knee from surgery she had in high school as well as a scar on her right palm from when she was accidentally stabbed during her time at the Farm. 
<p>&#9642; <b>PERSONALITY:</b> Finley is quite a complex person. Other than being a workaholic, she comes across as someone who enjoys knowing the sorts of secrets she knows. She’s also very dominant, something she learned early on while she was at University and something she honed during her time at the Farm. People always seem to think she’s a pushover because she’s shorter than a lot of her colleagues but the first time they try that they find out that she’s unwilling to take their shit. 
<p>Even when she’s not working her personality is still very  dominant. There are those times when she likes to be the life of the party or the centre of attention, but most of the times she’s content with ordering those around her. Finley has always been the sort who leads instead of following. During her time at the Farm she was constantly taking on the leader role and when she was meant to follow she would still take over because she felt those around her were incompetent. 
<p>She’s also the sort to say what is on her mind. Finley sees no point in beating around the bush and will bluntly tell someone what she thinks of them. More times than not she’s lost friends and work partners because of that. Only recently have they found people able to handle that about her. In her personal life, not many people consider her friend because of her very outgoing and dominating personality.
<p>&#9642; <b>LIKES:</b> Yoga, meditation, travelling, and learning languages. She also loves coming home and enjoying a nice glass of wine or other strong alcohol. Finley has quite the collection during her travels with the CIA.
<p>&#9642; <b>DISLIKES:</b> laziness, incompetence, inability to take control of a situation, idle conversations and parties.
<p>&#9642; <b>HOPES AND DREAMS:</b> Finley hadn’t thought much about the future other than to work her way up through the military. After 9/11 she honestly thought about joining the military and had the CIA not come calling she would have done that. Instead, she’s worked her way up through the CIA and being the head interrogation of special projects involving dreamsharing has been a dream come true for her.
<p>&#9642; <b>FEARS:</b> being alone, becoming a failure, death, losing herself in the dream
<p>&#9642; <b>STRENGTHS:</b> being a perfectionist, attention to detail, loyalty
<p>&#9642; <b>WEAKNESSES:</b> being a perfectionist, her loyalty, her determination, her workaholic nature
</div>

<p>
<center><h3>dreamsharing</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>Finley found out about dreamsharing when the military came to her university and looked for volunteers through the psychology program. There were strict guidelines in place and not everyone who applied made it to Project Somnasin, but Finley was one of the lucky ones. While most of those in the project were military men, they wanted civilians to see if they could handle it or if they could end up training those soldiers in the future. She aced all of their tests and while she took the pointman role, she did find out that she could forge if worse came to worse. It wasn’t her strength and the military saw that, but she did make an attempt to try it just in case there was need for her in the future.</div>
<p>
<p>
<center><h3>history</h3></center>
<p>Born to Sean and Cara Langston, Finley was an only child who wanted for nothing. Her parents noticed early on that she was smarter than her peers and picked up on things quicker than they did. Once they realised that they brought in tutors to constantly challenge her mind and to keep her from becoming bored. They refused to skip grades for her, wanting their child to have peers her own age. During her childhood Finley was frustrated with having the knowledge she did while her own peers were woefully lacking. And that frustration only grew the older she got. She never allowed it to manifest in physical ways. She’d never be the type who screamed out in frustration. Instead, she focused all of that frustration into making certain she never had to be frustrated again.
<p>Because of her tutoring as a child, Finley was able to graduate early from the University of Michigan with a degree in psychology. She hadn’t thought about the military but other than  going to graduate school there wasn’t much more she could do. There was also the fact that during her time at university she was involved in a secret experiment in conjunction with Project Somnasin. As a psychology student and teaching assistant she was involved in her fair share of projects. But her advisor mentioned another project where he felt her organisational skills would come in handy. Never did she think she would be involved in something like dreamsharing. No one even knew it existed.
<p>She flourished within the project and became one of their top prospects. To the point that the military was going to hire her to help train more soldiers to adjust to the world of war. It was a tempting offer and after graduation one she was thinking about taking. Finley got another job offer, one from the federal government and she took the summer after graduation to contemplate her options. She knew her parents would be supportive no matter what. Either decision would change her life and she couldn’t figure out which path she would take. Until that fateful September day… 
<p>September 11th changed in her ways she hadn’t thought. Her parents were killed when their plane slammed into the north tower in New York and that one event made her choice for her. While the military was her initial choice, she knew the government would allow her to find those who killed her parents. The CIA made her an offer she couldn’t refuse and after her time at the Farm she found herself assigned to a section where she could put her languages and psychology degree to use. Finley had no desire to work in the field and after returning to school to finish her masters, she managed to work her way up the interrogation chain. 
<p>Once she was in a position where she could suggest things, she suggested they bring in dreamsharing in an attempt to interrogate those they brought in during their 9/11 investigations. It took a lot of convincing, but in the end Finley was able to put together a special division that used dreamsharing to interrogate prisoners. Unfortunately, it meant bringing in those who were able to forge people in the dream, but given they worked at black sites and could easily bring in those they needed without them knowing. It would also open the door for other operations to use her techniques. Though, she will not let anyone else take credit for the fact that she’d brought this into the CIA and that it was quietly becoming known as the go to for those who didn’t break under their usual techniques.

<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>&#9642; Finley talks with her hands and sometimes uses sign language while holding a conversation. Most people just assume she’s using her hands to make a point, those who know sign will pick up on the rudimentary signs that she uses while holding a conversation.
<p>&#9642; Being an interrogator means she knows how to not only read people but manipulate them to give her the answers she needs. Unfortunately, it’s something she takes into her personal life as it’s become second nature to her.
<p>&#9642; She’s also left handed and when she’s exhausted you’ll find her in front of her computer with glasses on. Most of the time she wears contacts but after a long day at work she will take them out and wear glasses.
</div>

