<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>&#9642; <b>star wars:</b> yen’s ship is an <a href="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/swtor/images/2/2e/CA_Sith_Ship03_full.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20100821002213">imperial interceptor</a>. it was given to her by her master after her training was completed on dromund kaas. while it’s not the largest of ships, it works for her and has just enough <a href="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/8c/df/55/8cdf55309a485f7c6916cd1d800e2955.jpg">space</a> for herself and whatever companion she’s travelling with. it’s also something that she considers home seeing as she travels the galaxy from planet to planet without ever settling down. it hasn’t been easy for her in terms of upkeep but she’s made connections throughout the galaxy so that when something does go wrong she can call upon them to help. they are the only reason she’s been able to keep her ship running for as long as she has.
<p>&#9642; <b>star wars:</b> after yen completed her training on korriban, also known as moraband, she was given her first lightsaber. it is a double bladed lightsaber with a blood red kyber crystal. at the time she was thrilled with it and was proud to have earned not only the title of sith but the lightsaber that would signify her rank as one. as time went on, though, she wanted something different and crafted a <a href="https://starwars.fandom.com/wiki/Split_saber">split saber</a>. not only does it give her the ability to have two lightsabers but also flexibility in her kills. the crystal for this one is not the blood red crystal she received after her training on korriban, but a purple crystal that matches her eyes. after her training on dathomir the nightsisters gifted her the crystal to match the purple of her eyes.
</div>
