<center><h3>character traits</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>&#9642; Joe is muslim but one that doesn’t stick strictly to it. As it is a very personal religion he’s made it something that fits him and the life he lives. He makes a point to do morning and evening prayers whenever he can but he won’t punish himself if he’s unable to.
<p>&#9642; He’s a scion, a descendant of a wealthy merchant trading family and it’s why he knows more than just arabic
<p>&#9642; Joe can speak Persian, Arabic, Italian and English.
<p>&#9642; His combat style is swordsman tahtib. It is a traditional stick-fighting martial art. It originated in Egypt and evolved into an egyptian folk dance with a wooden stick.
<p>&#9642; While he does carry a sword, he is also comfortable with modern day weapons including pistols and rifles. 
<p>&#9642; At heart, Joe is a scholar and an artist. He’s only a soldier because he had no real choice. While he was a merchant he was dragged into fighting during the Crusades because of the horrors that were being inflicted on the world he lived in. if it hadn’t been for that he would’ve been content in the life he’d had
<p>&#9642; <b>He is not a crusader.</b> He was a merchant. His lifelong partner, Nicky, was a crusader. Joe was not. They met because of the fighting. And the fact that neither of them could die. After killing each other day after day for a week, if not longer, they came to terms. It was only the centuries they spent together that had them going from enemies to lovers to soulmates. 
</div>


<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>trivia</h3></center>
<p>&#9642; tbd 
<br />

<center><h3>headcanons</h3></center>
<div id="hc"><p>&#9642; <b>sweet vs savoury:</b> When it comes to food, Joe is the sort who prefers savoury over something sweet. Growing up in the Maghreb he was exposed to more savoury spices than sweet. Also, in the 11th century refined sugar wasn't a thing nor was sugar readily available like it is in modern times. Everything he ate would've been savoury and would've included spices like saffron, nutmeg, cinnamon, paprika, cloves, cumin, cayenne pepper, aniseed and black pepper. There were the occasional sweet things like oranges and figs, maybe even dates but they weren't what you would typically consider sweet. They were additions to the meal and to add some flavour to the rich meals that would've been his life. Even during his life with Andrew Underhill, their meals were more savoury than sweet, taking advantage of the local culture wherever they were stationed. 
<p>There are some exceptions, of course, and one of those just happened to be macarons. The sweets were created in the Renaissance and were things that Nicky introduced him to during their travels. It was something that quickly became a thing that Joe loved and would seek out whenever they were in a city with a bakery that provided international treats.. When they started to have buttercream, jam or ganache sandwiched between in the them in the 1930s he knew that he was in love with the sandwich treats. He has no particular favourite when it comes to flavours, but he does secretly enjoy coconut, orange and other fruit flavours, and will never turn them down should they be offered. Unfortunately, they also tend to be used as blackmail, mostly by Nicky, because of his weakness for them.
</div>

<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>verses</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>main verse</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nleft"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/NSRayQg.png"></div>
<b>we fight for what we think is right</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → yusuf ⸥ ❛ v; we fight for what we think is right ❜ || main">threads</a>: covers from the crusades up through the day that yusuf eventually dies. This is a catchall verse and is compatible with most all fandoms. It will also blend elements from the movies with certain elements from the comics. arcs from yusuf's early years, the movie, and post movie are available. Given the fandom and the content, this verse will contain certain <b>triggers</b> and will be tagged appropriately<br /><br />
</div>
<p>
<center><h3>shadowhunters</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nright"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/NSRayQg.png"></div>
<b>the world isn’t getting any better; it’s getting worse</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → yusuf ⸥ ❛ v; the world isn’t getting any better; it’s getting worse ❜ || shadowhunters">threads</a>:  <i>Sabra Mostafa-Moussa</i>. It was a name that he’d used only once, during one of his times in Africa and the life that followed. After losing Nicolò far too soon, he spent that time in mourning travelling the world and occasionally working with Andy and Booker. It was painful for him to be with them as it was a reminder of the times when he and Nicky would work together. But Africa was one of the times when he worked on his own and when he met one Andrew Underhill. It was the last thing he expected and he fell hard for him. After Kinshasa they had several postings and while life in the shadow world was different, it was the sort of thing he needed. Travelling from post to post he knew it wouldn’t last forever. In time they would notice Andrew growing old while he didn’t. Joe knew eventually he’d have to leave. He just never thought it would be as it had been. Demons weren’t his favourite way to die but it saved his partner and the Institute. While they never found proof of his death, he had survived the attack and left Giza, rejoining his friends. Only when they went to New York did his past come to haunt him in a way he never expected. this is a <b>single ship</b> verse with <b>affcgato</b><br /><br />
</div>
