<p>
<center><h3>the old guard</h3></center>
<p>
<div id="verse">
<div id="nright"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/622MmUw.png"></div>
<b>nothing that lives lives forever</b> &mdash; <a href="/tagged/⸢ verse → hux ⸥ ❛ v; nothing that lives lives forever ❜ || the old guard">threads</a>: Life had always been a battle for Cadeyrn. Born at the dawn of a new millenia, he was tasked with helping his Iceni defeat the Romans. Under Boudica they tried their hardest and in 60AD Cadeyrn came to the realisation he wasn’t the mortal soldier he’d always thought he was. His death came at the hands of a Roman Soldier and having been found by Andromache accepted his new life as an immortal. It hadn’t been easy but given the amount of wars that showed up, he knew that his life would be content. Throughout the ages Cadeyrn found himself in battle after battle, unable to resist the urge and much to Andromache’s chagrin. The more time he spent with her, though, the more he found their work fulfilling. Much more than a battle ever would.
</div>
<br /> <br /><br />
</li>

