<!-- julia pennyworth -->


<div id="24" class="popup_block">
<div id="popside">

<div id="popsideimage"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/5tZjfqj.png"></div> <!-- change the image on the popup sidebar -->

<ul id="poptabs">
     <li class="active" style="width:100px">biography</li>
		
     <li style="width:100px">headcanons</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">verses</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">connections</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">ships</li>
</ul>  

</div> 

<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>biography</h4>
<br />
<center><h3>the file</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Julia Pennyworth is a disavowed spy of the Special Reconnaissance Regiment, known under the code-name Tuxedo One. She is the daughter of Alfred Pennyworth, the goddaughter of the late Lucius Fox, a longtime friend of Bruce Wayne and Luke Fox, and the ex-girlfriend/close friend of Kate Kane and Sophie Moore.
<p>Julia briefly posed as Batwoman to fool the agents of Crows Security and divert their attention away from Kate. Later after helping them uncover the corruption among their ranks, she joined the Crows and was charged to lead their new strike team together with Sophie, with whom she began a relationship.
<p>However, after Kate's disappearance, Julia's relationship with Sophie began to fall apart due to being secretive with the latter on knowing Kate's identity as Batwoman.
<p>Julia traveled to various places to investigate Kate's disappearance, which caught Enigma's attention, which made Julia forget her last memories and stop investigating. Julia then "found" pieces of bone that matched Kate's DNA in Blüdhaven, which made her think Kate was dead.
<p>Eventually, Julia discovered that she had memories missing; Alice then called her to help find Enigma, the hypnotist who Julia found out was Dr Evelyn Rhyme. When Julia confronts Evelyn at the base of the Crows, she is sedated and had her memories erased again, and this time Enigma made her ask for a transfer to Berlin.
</div>
<br />
<br />
<center><h3>personality</h3></center>
<div id="bio"><p>Julia appears as a charming and confident woman. She is proven to be a loyal friend to Kate Kane, whom she affectionately calls "luv" - something later she started to do with Sophie Moore as well. Julia helped Kate protect her secret identity, even risking her life in the process. When she learned that Sophie was in danger, Julia immediately took the bullet while tackling her out of the line of fire, despite not knowing Sophie. She also has a good sense of humor and is extremely sarcastic, loving to tease Kate and often engages in friendly bickering with her. Although she has a tendency to keep vital information to herself in order to protect her loved ones, often seeming to act shady, Julia always has the best of intentions and carries no qualms in being truthful and completely open when really needed.
<p>Julia is quite friendly and easygoing, having no problem discussing her intimate relationships with others and harbors no hard feelings towards her exes. However, she was visibly offended when Kate questioned her loyalty and stated that she didn't trust her.
<p>Julia has a treacherous side to her if she believes necessary, as she deceived Kate during their first meeting, hiding that Bruce Wayne had sent her to keep an eye on his cousin. Julia also seems keen to hide more darker secrets about herself, such as that she was no longer working for the SRR since operating for Safiyah Sohail. When Johnny Sabatino's men discovered this after kidnapping her, Julia ruthlessly killed both her captors to keep it hidden. Julia only revealed that she agreed to work with Safiyah to protect Kate from the Rifle when having no choice.
</div>
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

